title: Selfish Sue
author: brandon
text: one summer at camp creepinadaloo there was a girl named sue magoo.   she was pretty,  she was witty so at first her bunkmates thought that this camper from the city could teach them quite a lot!  but sue magoo didnâ’t care to talk or play with anyone there.   not only was she bossy,  rude,  and mean,  she never helped with the bunkâ’s chores,  like sorting laundry or sweeping floorsâ— and expected to be treated like a queen!  â“oh sue magoo, â” they asked,  â“wonâ’t you share the candies your parents sent you from the fair?â”  but sue magoo just turned her nose up and said,  â“no way! these sweets are just for me!â” and ate them till she almost threw up! her bunkmates were far from happy.   they said,  â“oh that terrible sue magoo,  she's just selfish,  through and through!â”  then one day while they hiked up a trail the campers came upon a cave.  from deep inside a voice came â– a very scary wail! it said,  â“i have riches great for you,  if you are very brave!â”  naturally sue magoo declared that she would go: â“stand aside,  iâ’ll go inside,  iâ’m the best you know!â”  the campers knew she would not share the riches promised by the voice but since it was dark and scary in there they agreed on sue magoo for their choice.   so sue magoo boldy walked into the hole and found it occupied by a terrifying troll!  ''i see you come alone, '' the creepy ogre said.  ''it's plain to see you're so greedy,  you weren't thinking with your head! now i will make you sorry,  yes indeedy!''  and before sue magoo could say boo the troll opened wide and bit her in two!   and late at night in camp creepindaloo you can still hear the cries of selfish sue.

text: have you ever been in a place where everyone is the same? where people ponder and sing? where life is a storybook,  just as predictable as a school day? everyone knows everything,  and nothing is different any day or time? where the story of life just continues and never ends? where the waters of the nile flow just as fast as a racecar never needing to stop? and you are in the middle,  watching all of this confusion,  and no one seems to mind? no one stopping.   no one listening to what you have to say? when the night turns to day and life is just as confusing as… the puzzle with no picture.  i've heard if this place,  it's called my life,  it's filled with confusion.  and has no light,   it's a place i like to call a confusing world,  everything is moving,  not stopping,  never ending,  the noise gets louder and louder,  and it pounds deep into your heart,  and you are lost in confusion?
